posted on 2003-12-08, 00:00 authored by Susan E. Gibson, Craig Johnstone, Jennifer A. Loch, Jonathan W. Steed, Andrea Stevenazzi

N-Heterocyclic carbene derivatives of dicobalt octacarbonyl have been synthesized for the first time and tested in the PausonâKhand reaction. Two complexes with both NHC and PPh3 ligands represent the only examples of structurally characterized dicobalt hexacarbonyl complexes with two different non-CO ligands.
